So most probably the author has Git for Windows installed with the option of adding Unix tools (ls is also there) to the Path (this option is offered during the Git for Windows installation).

Plus, in some areas, water is supplied by water tanks. Sure, they may hold a million gallons, but how fast does that go away when a major fire is being fought?
